    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339264' state='<u>battle</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='204'&gt;<u>tsousa</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Elements&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='2_4' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='1' ownerId='204' direction='S' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='8_1' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='0' ownerId='1339159' direction='N' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
  &lt;/Elements&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Beachte das der Status von <u>deploy</u> zu <u>battle</u> gewechselt hat. Jetzt erhälst du die 
    aktuelle [GameBoard] Disposition, jede Einheiten-Gruppe, Anzahl, Koordinate, etc.
    Nachdem deine Spielzüge kalkuliert wurden, müsstest du deine Antworten zurücksenden zum Spiel, 
    indem du die angegebene URL benutzt <u>ResponseUrl</u>. Eine Beispiel-URL würde sein:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botbattle</u>&amp;id=<u>1111</u>&amp;moves=<u>r:7_3-n-w;b:7_3-7_2;m:8_3-8_2-5-n;b:8_2-7_2;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    
    Der <u>moves</u> Parameter ist wie eine Liste von Spielzügen mit der folgenden Syntax:
    
    <table class=" + '"' + @"table" + '"' + @" style=" + '"' + @"width: 100%; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" + '"' + @"><tbody><tr><th>Type</th><th>Syntax</th><th>Description</th></tr><tr><td>Move</td><td><pre>m:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>destination_coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u>-<u>direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Moves a unit group from one square to another adjacent square</td></tr><tr><td>Rotate</td><td><pre>r:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>current_direction</u>-<u>next_direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Rotates a unit group; direction can be: N, S, E and W</td></tr><tr><td>Attack</td><td><pre>b:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>target_coordinate</u>;</pre></td><td>Attacks the adversary unit group</td></tr></tbody></table>
    
    Dann ist die Runde deines Gegners. Wenn er fertig ist, erhälst du den neuen [GameBoard] Status 
    und du musst dann weitere Spielzüge machen. Das geht so weiter bis die Schalcht nicht vorbei ist. 
    Beachte dass deine Spielzüge nicht mehr als 6 [MovPoints] kosten dürfen.
    
    <a name=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Mehr Information</h2>
    Wenn du Fragen oder Vorschläge hast kontaktiere uns bitte, wir würden dir gerne weiterhelfen.
  </div>");
			Add("en", "BattleAPIInfo_Part1", @"<div class=" + '"' + @"content" + '"' + @">
    The <b>Battle API</b> allows third party applications to play battles on [OB] as a <i>bot</i>. You may use this API to create artificial
    intelligence bots or game clients that'll be able to battle with other players or bots on the [GameBoard]. Example of a battle:
    
    <img src=" + '"' + @"/Resources/Images/Battle.png" + '"' + @" class=" + '"' + @"block" + '"' + @" /><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Apply" + '"' + @">How to Apply</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Overview" + '"' + @">Overview</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#AskBattles" + '"' + @">Ask For Battles</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Deploy" + '"' + @">Deploy</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#TurnMoves" + '"' + @">Turn Moves</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#More" + '"' + @">More Information</a></li></ul><a name=" + '"' + @"Apply" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"apply" + '"' + @"></a><h2>How to Apply</h2>
    In order to be able to develop an application using the Battle API, you'll have to contact us. Then we will prepare the development environment
    for you and get you started.
    <p />
    You may contact us using the <a href=" + '"' + @"mailto:manual@orionsbelt.eu" + '"' + @">manual@orionsbelt.eu</a> mail.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Overview</h2>
    The Battle API is very simple to use. You may create an application that will comunicate with [OB] and send/receive moves and battle states.
    You'll have to code your application to perform deploys and turns. The basic interaction is the following:
    <ul><li>#1 You ask the server for battles, and receive a XML file with the battles you have to play</li><li>#2 For each battle received you'll send a HTTP reques to a provided URL with a deploy or moves</li><li>#3 Wait a while and then return to step #1</li></ul><p />
    You have available a XML file with the complete <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. When we configure your bot/client, you'll
    be able to create a [Friendly] with it and try your bot in action.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Ask For Battles</h2>
    The first time you ask for battles, you won't get any. You'll have to create a [Friendly] with your bot, and only then you'll get some battles
    to play. To ask for battles you'll have to make an HTTP request to:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">http://<u>server</u>.orionsbelt.eu/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx?type=<u>botGetBattles</u>&amp;botId=<u>1111</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>

    Note that you'll have to send the request for the right server. You'll have a bot per server, so if you're registered on more than one server you'll have to act
    accordinally. You also have to give the bot ID and the bot verification code.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Deploy</h2>
    The first part of the battle is the [Deploy]. When you request battles using the previous URL you'll receive something like:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339260' state='<u>deploy</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='203'&gt;<u>nunos</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;Bot001&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Units&gt;
    &lt;Unit quantity='10' name='Raptor' code='rp' /&gt;
  &lt;/Units&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    This is a very simple battle between <u>Bot001</u> and <u>nunos</u>, and you'd have to deploy now. The combat [Fleet] only has the [Raptor], no more [CombatUnits]
    are present. You'd now have to make a request to <u>ResponseUrl</u> indicating how you'd like to [Deploy]:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botdeploy</u>&amp;id=<u>1234</u>&amp;moves=<u>p:rp-8_1-2;p:rp-8_2-8;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    The <u>moves</u> parameter is the most important one and has the following format:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">p:<u>unit_code</u>-<u>coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u></pre>
    You'd have to build a string like this one for each unit block on the deploy zone. You have the unit codes on the <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. After invoking
    the correctly formed URL, the battle will continue.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Turn Moves</h2>
    After the deploy you may ask again for your battles, and you will now have to play your moves. Note that on these examples only a battle is being returned, but
    if you had several battles to play, you'd receive several &lt;Battle/&gt; elements. When's your turn to play, you'll receive something like:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339264' state='<u>battle</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='204'&gt;<u>tsousa</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Elements&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='2_4' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='1' ownerId='204' direction='S' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='8_1' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='0' ownerId='1339159' direction='N' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
  &lt;/Elements&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Note that the state changed from <u>deploy</u> to <u>battle</u>. Now you receive the current [GameBoard] disposition, each unit group, quantity, coordinate, etc.
    After calculating your moves, you'd have to send your response again to the game, using the given <u>ResponseUrl</u>. An example URL would be:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botbattle</u>&amp;id=<u>1111</u>&amp;moves=<u>r:7_3-n-w;b:7_3-7_2;m:8_3-8_2-5-n;b:8_2-7_2;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    
    The <u>moves</u> parameter is again a list of moves with the following syntax:
    
    <table class=" + '"' + @"table" + '"' + @" style=" + '"' + @"width:100%;margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;" + '"' + @"><tr><th>Type</th><th>Syntax</th><th>Description</th></tr><tr><td>Move</td><td><pre>m:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>destination_coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u>-<u>direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Moves a unit group from one square to another adjacent square</td></tr><tr><td>Rotate</td><td><pre>r:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>current_direction</u>-<u>next_direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Rotates a unit group; direction can be: N, S, E and W</td></tr><tr><td>Attack</td><td><pre>b:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>target_coordinate</u>;</pre></td><td>Attacks the adversary unit group</td></tr></table>
    
    Then it's your opponents turn to play. When he's done, you'll receive the new [GameBoard] state and you have to make more moves. This continues until
    the battle isn't finished. Note that your movements can't spend more than 6 [MovPoints].
    
    <a name=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @"></a><h2>More Information</h2>
    If you have any questions or suggestions please contact us and we'll be happy to help you.
  </div>");
			Add("fr", "BattleAPIInfo_Part1", @"<div class=" + '"' + @"content" + '"' + @">
    L'<b>API de Combat</b> permet à un tierce partie extérieur d'utiliser les logiciels pour jouer des combats sur [OB] contre <i>" + '"' + @"qu'escadrlle préprogrammé</i>. Vous pouvez utiliser cet API pour créer des escadrilles ayant une intelligence artificielle (communément appelés E.A.I.) ou créer des " + '"' + @"Game clients" + '"' + @" capable de combattre d'autres joueurs ou d'autres E.A.I. sur le You may use this API to create artificial [GameBoard]. Exemple de bataille:
    
    <img src=" + '"' + @"/Resources/Images/Battle.png" + '"' + @" class=" + '"' + @"block" + '"' + @" /><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Apply" + '"' + @">How to Apply</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Overview" + '"' + @">Overview</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#AskBattles" + '"' + @">Ask For Battles</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Deploy" + '"' + @">Deploy</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#TurnMoves" + '"' + @">Turn Moves</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#More" + '"' + @">More Information</a></li></ul><a name=" + '"' + @"Apply" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"apply" + '"' + @"></a><h2>How to Apply</h2>
    Pour pouvoir développer un logiciel en utilisant l'API de combat, vous devez nous contacter. Nous pourrons ensuite vous préparer un environnement de création et vous aider à débuter.
    <p>
    Vous pouvez nous contecter en utilisant ce courriel: <a href=" + '"' + @"mailto:manual@orionsbelt.eu" + '"' + @">manual@orionsbelt.eu</a><a name=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @"></a></p><h2>Overview</h2>
    L'API de combat est très simple à utiliser. Vous pouvez créer un logociel en communication avec avec[OB] pour envoyer et recevoir les mouvements et l'état du combat. and send/receive moves and battle states.
    Vous devrez coder le logiciel pour exécuter les déploiments et les tours. L'interation principales est celle-ci:
    <ul><li>#1 Vous demandez au serveur pour des combats et vous recevez un fichier XML avec les batailles que vous devez jouer.</li><li>#2 Pour chaque bataille reçu, vous allez envoyer une demande HTTP à l'URL qui vous sera fournit aves un déploiement ou les mouvements.</li><li>#3 Attendez un momment et répéter l'étape #1.</li></ul><p>
    Vous avez un fichier XML disponible avec les<a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">spécifications des unités</a>. Lorsque nous aurons configuré votre E.A.I/" + '"' + @"client" + '"' + @", vous serez capale de créer un [Friendly] avec lui et le tester en action.
    <a name=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @"></a></p><h2>Ask For Battles</h2>
    La première que vous ferez une demande pour un combat, Il n'y en aura pas. Vous devrez d'abord créer un [Friendly] avec votre E.A.I. pour ensuite pouvoir jouer des batailles. La demande en HTTP pour les batailles doivent se faire à:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">http://<u>server</u>.orionsbelt.eu/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx?type=<u>botGetBattles</u>&amp;botId=<u>1111</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>

    Notez que vous devez envoyer votre demande directement pour le bon serveur. Vous aurez un E.A.I. par serveur, alors si vous êtes enregistré à plus d'un serveur, vous devrez agir en conséquence. Vous devez aussi donner L'identification de votre E.A.I. ainsi que son ode de vérification.
    <a name=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Deploy</h2>
    La première partie de la bataille est le déploiment. Quand vous faites une demande pour des combats en utilisant l'URL précédent, vous recevrez quelque chose comme:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339260' state='<u>deploy</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='203'&gt;<u>nunos</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;Bot001&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Units&gt;
    &lt;Unit quantity='10' name='Raptor' code='rp' /&gt;
  &lt;/Units&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Voici une bataille très simple entre <u>E.A.I.001</u> et <u>nunos</u>, et vous devez maintenat faire le déploiement. L'[Fleet] de combat a seulement des [Raptor], aucune autre [CombatUnits]
    est présente. Vous auriez à faire une demande à <u>RéponseUrl</u> indiquant vous aimerez votre [Deploy]:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botdeploy</u>&amp;id=<u>1234</u>&amp;moves=<u>p:rp-8_1-2;p:rp-8_2-8;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    The <u>moves</u> Ce paramètre est le plus important et a le format suivant:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">p:<u>unit_code</u>-<u>coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u></pre>
    Vous auriez à construire un fil comme celui-çi pour chaque case où il y a une unité lors du déploiement. Vous avez les codes des unités sur You have the unit codes on the <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. Après avoir invoquer le format correcte URL, le combat continue.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Turn Moves</h2>
    Après le déploiment, vous pouvez encore demander pour les combats et vous devrez maintenant exécuter vos mouvements.Notez que sur cet example il y a seulement une bataile, mais si vous en auriez plusieurs, vous recevrez plusieurs éléments de N &lt;Bataille/&gt;. Quand c?est à votre tour de jouer, vous recevrez:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339264' state='<u>battle</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='204'&gt;<u>tsousa</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Elements&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='2_4' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='1' ownerId='204' direction='S' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='8_1' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='0' ownerId='1339159' direction='N' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
  &lt;/Elements&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Notez que l?état a changé de <u>déploiment</u> to <u>combat</u>. Vous recevez maintenant les dispositions actuelles du [GameBoard], de chaque groupe d?unités, la quantité, les coordonées, etc.
    Après avoir calculé vos mouvements, vous devriez envoyer votre réponse encore une fois au jeu en utilisant la <u>RéponseURL</u>. Un exemple d?URL serait:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botbattle</u>&amp;id=<u>1111</u>&amp;moves=<u>r:7_3-n-w;b:7_3-7_2;m:8_3-8_2-5-n;b:8_2-7_2;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    
    Le paramètre de <u>mouvement</u> est encore une liste de mouvements avec la syntaxe suivante:
    
    <table class=" + '"' + @"table" + '"' + @" style=" + '"' + @"width: 100%; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" + '"' + @"><tbody><tr><th>Type</th><th>Syntax</th><th>Description</th></tr><tr><td>Move</td><td><pre>m:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>destination_coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u>-<u>direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Bouge un groupe d?unité d?une case à une autre adjacente.</td></tr><tr><td>Rotate</td><td><pre>r:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>current_direction</u>-<u>next_direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Change la direction d?un groupe; les possibilités étant: N, S, E et O</td></tr><tr><td>Attack</td><td><pre>b:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>target_coordinate</u>;</pre></td><td>Attacks the adversary unit group</td></tr></tbody></table>
    
    C?est ensuite le tour à vos adversaires de jouer. Quand il a terminé, vous recevrez le nouveau état du [GameBoard] et pourrez faire de nouveaux mouvements. Cela continue jusqu?a ce que la bataille est terminé. À noter que vous ne pouvez pas dépenser plus de 6 [MovPoints].
    
    <a name=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @"></a><h2>More Information</h2>
    Si jamais vous avez des questions ou suggestions, nous serons heureux de vous aider. Il suffit de nous contacter.
  </div>");
			Add("hr", "BattleAPIInfo_Part1", @"<div class=" + '"' + @"content" + '"' + @">
    The <b>Battle API</b> allows third party applications to play battles on [OB] as a <i>bot</i>. You may use this API to create artificial
    intelligence bots or game clients that'll be able to battle with other players or bots on the [GameBoard]. Example of a battle:
    
    <img src=" + '"' + @"/Resources/Images/Battle.png" + '"' + @" class=" + '"' + @"block" + '"' + @" /><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Apply" + '"' + @">How to Apply</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Overview" + '"' + @">Overview</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#AskBattles" + '"' + @">Ask For Battles</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Deploy" + '"' + @">Deploy</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#TurnMoves" + '"' + @">Turn Moves</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#More" + '"' + @">More Information</a></li></ul><a name=" + '"' + @"Apply" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"apply" + '"' + @"></a><h2>How to Apply</h2>
    In order to be able to develop an application using the Battle API, you'll have to contact us. Then we will prepare the development environment
    for you and get you started.
    <p />
    You may contact us using the <a href=" + '"' + @"mailto:manual@orionsbelt.eu" + '"' + @">manual@orionsbelt.eu</a> mail.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Overview</h2>
    The Battle API is very simple to use. You may create an application that will comunicate with [OB] and send/receive moves and battle states.
    You'll have to code your application to perform deploys and turns. The basic interaction is the following:
    <ul><li>#1 You ask the server for battles, and receive a XML file with the battles you have to play</li><li>#2 For each battle received you'll send a HTTP reques to a provided URL with a deploy or moves</li><li>#3 Wait a while and then return to step #1</li></ul><p />
    You have available a XML file with the complete <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. When we configure your bot/client, you'll
    be able to create a [Friendly] with it and try your bot in action.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Ask For Battles</h2>
    The first time you ask for battles, you won't get any. You'll have to create a [Friendly] with your bot, and only then you'll get some battles
    to play. To ask for battles you'll have to make an HTTP request to:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">http://<u>server</u>.orionsbelt.eu/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx?type=<u>botGetBattles</u>&amp;botId=<u>1111</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>

    Note that you'll have to send the request for the right server. You'll have a bot per server, so if you're registered on more than one server you'll have to act
    accordinally. You also have to give the bot ID and the bot verification code.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Deploy</h2>
    The first part of the battle is the [Deploy]. When you request battles using the previous URL you'll receive something like:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339260' state='<u>deploy</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='203'&gt;<u>nunos</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;Bot001&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Units&gt;
    &lt;Unit quantity='10' name='Raptor' code='rp' /&gt;
  &lt;/Units&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    This is a very simple battle between <u>Bot001</u> and <u>nunos</u>, and you'd have to deploy now. The combat [Fleet] only has the [Raptor], no more [CombatUnits]
    are present. You'd now have to make a request to <u>ResponseUrl</u> indicating how you'd like to [Deploy]:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botdeploy</u>&amp;id=<u>1234</u>&amp;moves=<u>p:rp-8_1-2;p:rp-8_2-8;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    The <u>moves</u> parameter is the most important one and has the following format:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">p:<u>unit_code</u>-<u>coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u></pre>
    You'd have to build a string like this one for each unit block on the deploy zone. You have the unit codes on the <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. After invoking
    the correctly formed URL, the battle will continue.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Turn Moves</h2>
    After the deploy you may ask again for your battles, and you will now have to play your moves. Note that on these examples only a battle is being returned, but
    if you had several battles to play, you'd receive several &lt;Battle/&gt; elements. When's your turn to play, you'll receive something like:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339264' state='<u>battle</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='204'&gt;<u>tsousa</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Elements&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='2_4' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='1' ownerId='204' direction='S' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='8_1' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='0' ownerId='1339159' direction='N' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
  &lt;/Elements&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Note that the state changed from <u>deploy</u> to <u>battle</u>. Now you receive the current [GameBoard] disposition, each unit group, quantity, coordinate, etc.
    After calculating your moves, you'd have to send your response again to the game, using the given <u>ResponseUrl</u>. An example URL would be:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botbattle</u>&amp;id=<u>1111</u>&amp;moves=<u>r:7_3-n-w;b:7_3-7_2;m:8_3-8_2-5-n;b:8_2-7_2;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    
    The <u>moves</u> parameter is again a list of moves with the following syntax:
    
    <table class=" + '"' + @"table" + '"' + @" style=" + '"' + @"width:100%;margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;" + '"' + @"><tr><th>Type</th><th>Syntax</th><th>Description</th></tr><tr><td>Move</td><td><pre>m:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>destination_coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u>-<u>direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Moves a unit group from one square to another adjacent square</td></tr><tr><td>Rotate</td><td><pre>r:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>current_direction</u>-<u>next_direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Rotates a unit group; direction can be: N, S, E and W</td></tr><tr><td>Attack</td><td><pre>b:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>target_coordinate</u>;</pre></td><td>Attacks the adversary unit group</td></tr></table>
    
    Then it's your opponents turn to play. When he's done, you'll receive the new [GameBoard] state and you have to make more moves. This continues until
    the battle isn't finished. Note that your movements can't spend more than 6 [MovPoints].
    
    <a name=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @"></a><h2>More Information</h2>
    If you have any questions or suggestions please contact us and we'll be happy to help you.
  </div>");
			Add("hu", "BattleAPIInfo_Part1", @"<div class=" + '"' + @"content" + '"' + @">
    A <b>Battle API</b> lehetőséget nyújt egy harmadik fél számára hogy részt vegyenek a csatában [OB] mint <i>bot</i>. Felhasználhatod az API-t, hogy mesterséges
    intelligenciával rednelkező bot-okat kreálj, vagy játék klienseket amelyek képesek lesznek harcolni más játékosokkal vagy bot-okkal a [GameBoard]-on. Példa a csatára:
    
    <img src=" + '"' + @"/Resources/Images/Battle.png" + '"' + @" class=" + '"' + @"block" + '"' + @" /><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Apply" + '"' + @">How to Apply</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Overview" + '"' + @">Overview</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#AskBattles" + '"' + @">Ask For Battles</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Deploy" + '"' + @">Deploy</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#TurnMoves" + '"' + @">Turn Moves</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#More" + '"' + @">More Information</a></li></ul><a name=" + '"' + @"Apply" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"apply" + '"' + @"></a><h2>How to Apply</h2>
    Ahhoz, hogy kifejlessz egy alkalmazást Csata API felhasználásaval, kapcsolatba kell lépned velünk. Ezek után elkészítjük neked a fejlesztési környezetet
    hogy azonnal elkezdhesd.
    <p />
    Kapcsolatba tudsz velünk lépni a <a href=" + '"' + @"mailto:manual@orionsbelt.eu" + '"' + @">manual@orionsbelt.eu</a> e-mailen.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Overview</h2>
    A Battle API-t nagyon egyszerű használni. Létrehozhatsz olyan alkalmazást amely az [OB]-val kommunikál és küld/fogad mozgásokat és csata állapotokat.
    Kódolnod kell az alkalmazásodat, hogy  végrhajtson telepítést és köröket. Az alapvető kölcsönhatás a következő:
    <ul><li>#1 Csatákat kérsz a Szervertől, és kapsz egy XML fájlt a csatákkal amiket le kell játszanod</li><li>#2 Minden egyes fogadott csatáért elküldesz egy HTTP igényt egy megadott URL-re egy telepítéssel vagy mozgásokkal</li><li>#3 Várj egy darabig, majd térj vissza az #1 lépéshez</li></ul><p />
    Elérhető egy XML fájl a teljes<a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. Amikor konfigurálod a saját bot-ot/klienst, létrehozhatsz
    vele egy [Friendly] bot-ot és kipróbálhatod a bot-odat éles helyzetben.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Ask For Battles</h2>
    Az első alkalommal amikor csatát kérsz, nem fogsz kapni egyet sem. Létre kell hoznod egy [Friendly]-t a bot-oddal, és csak ez után kapsz csatákat.
    Ahhoz hogy csatát kérj létre kell hoznod egy HTTP igénylést itt:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">http://<u>server</u>.orionsbelt.eu/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx?type=<u>botGetBattles</u>&amp;botId=<u>1111</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>

    Vigyázz hogy az igénylést a megfelelő szervernek küld. Szerverenként egy bot-od van, így amennyiben több szerveren is regisztrálvan vagy ennek megfelelően
    kell cselekedned. Ezenkívül meg kell adnod a bot ID-t és az érvényesítő kódot.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Deploy</h2>
   A játék első része a [Deploy]. Amikor csatát igényelsz a fentebbi URL-en valami ilyesmit fogsz kapni:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339260' state='<u>deploy</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='203'&gt;<u>nunos</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;Bot001&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Units&gt;
    &lt;Unit quantity='10' name='Raptor' code='rp' /&gt;
  &lt;/Units&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Ez egy nagyon egyszerű csata <u>Bot001</u> és <u>nunos</u> között, és most kellene egységeket telepítened. A harci [Fleet] csak a [Raptor]-al rendelkezik, nincs több [CombatUnits]
    jelen. Most kellene egy igénylést csinálnod <u>ResponseUrl</u> megadva, hogy hogyan szeretnél [Deploy]:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botdeploy</u>&amp;id=<u>1234</u>&amp;moves=<u>p:rp-8_1-2;p:rp-8_2-8;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    A <u>moves</u> paraméter a legfontosabb és a következő formátummal rendelkezik:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">p:<u>unit_code</u>-<u>coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u></pre>
    Egy vonalat kellene kiépítened mint ez, minden egyes egység csoportnak a telepítési zónán. Az egység kódokat megtalálod a <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. A megfelelő
    URL formátul létrehozása után, a csata folytatódni fog.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Turn Moves</h2>
    A telepítés után ismét kérheted a csatáidat és ezek után már a játszanod kell a csatát. Ezeken a példákon csak egy csata tár vissza, de
    ha számos játszani való csatád volt, akkor különböző &lt;Battle/&gt; elemeket kapnál. Amikor te következel valami ilyesmit kapsz:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339264' state='<u>battle</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='204'&gt;<u>tsousa</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Elements&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='2_4' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='1' ownerId='204' direction='S' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='8_1' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='0' ownerId='1339159' direction='N' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
  &lt;/Elements&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    A státsuz megváltozott <u>deploy</u>-ről <u>battle</u>-ra. Megkapod az aktuális [GameBoard] elrendezést,minden egyes egység csoportot, mennyiséget, koordinátát, stb.
    Miután kiszámoltad a mozdulataidat, el kell küldened a válaszlépáseidet, felhasználva a megadott <u>ResponseUrl</u>. Egy példa az URL-re:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botbattle</u>&amp;id=<u>1111</u>&amp;moves=<u>r:7_3-n-w;b:7_3-7_2;m:8_3-8_2-5-n;b:8_2-7_2;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    
    A <u>moves</u> paraméter mozgások listája a következő szintaxissal:
    
    <table class=" + '"' + @"table" + '"' + @" style=" + '"' + @"width:100%;margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;" + '"' + @"><tr><th>Type</th><th>Syntax</th><th>Description</th></tr><tr><td>Move</td><td><pre>m:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>destination_coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u>-<u>direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Mozgtja az egységet egyik helyről a kijelölt másikra</td></tr><tr><td>Rotate</td><td><pre>r:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>current_direction</u>-<u>next_direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Forgatja az egységet; irány lehet: N, S, E and W</td></tr><tr><td>Attack</td><td><pre>b:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>target_coordinate</u>;</pre></td><td>ellenséges egység támadása</td></tr></table>
    
    Ezután az ellenfeled következik. Amikor végzett, megkapod az új [GameBoard] állást és ezután te következel a körben. Ez addig folytatódik amíg
    a csata be nem fejeződik. Mozgásaid nem lehetnek többek 6 [MovPoints]-nál.
    
    <a name=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @"></a><h2>More Information</h2>
    Amennyiben kérdésed vagy javaslatod van lépj velünk kapcsolatba, örömmel segítünk.
  </div>");
			Add("it", "BattleAPIInfo_Part1", @"<div class=" + '"' + @"content" + '"' + @">
    L' <b>API delle Battaglie</b> permette ad applicazioni terze di combattere su [OB] come <i>bot</i>. Puoi usare questa API per creare bot con intelligenze artificiali o client di gioco in grado di combattere con altri giocatori o altri bot sulla [GameBoard]. Esempio di battaglia:
    
    <img src=" + '"' + @"/Resources/Images/Battle.png" + '"' + @" class=" + '"' + @"block" + '"' + @" /><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Apply" + '"' + @">How to Apply</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Overview" + '"' + @">Overview</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#AskBattles" + '"' + @">Ask For Battles</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Deploy" + '"' + @">Deploy</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#TurnMoves" + '"' + @">Turn Moves</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#More" + '"' + @">More Information</a></li></ul><a name=" + '"' + @"Apply" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"apply" + '"' + @"></a><h2>How to Apply</h2>
    Per sviluppare un'applicazione usando l'API delle Battaglie devi prima contattarci. Noi prepareremo l'ambiente di sviluppo e ti aiuteremo a iniziare.
    <p>
    Puoi contattarci a questa email: <a href=" + '"' + @"mailto:manual@orionsbelt.eu" + '"' + @">manual@orionsbelt.eu</a>.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @"></a></p><h2>Panoramica</h2>
    L'API delle Battaglie è molto semplice da usare. Puoi creare un'applicazione che comunichi con [OB] e che mandi/riceva le mosse e gli stati della battaglia.
    Dovrai programmare la tua applicazione per eseguire gli schieramenti della flotta e i turni. La base dell'interazione è questa:
    <ul><li>#1 Chiedi al server le battaglie e ricevi un XML con le battaglie che devi giocare.</li><li>#2 Per ogni battaglia ricevuta mandi una richiesta HTTP ad un URL, che ti viene dato, con lo schieramento o i movimenti del turno.</li><li>#3 Aspetta un po' e torna al passo 1</li></ul><p>
    È disponibile un XML con le <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">Specifiche delle Unità</a>. Quando configureremo il tuo bot/client, potrai creare una [Friendly] con lui per provarlo in battaglia.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @"></a></p><h2>Richiesta Battaglie</h2>
    La prima volta che chiedi le battaglie al server, non ne ricevi. Devi prima creare una [Friendly] col tuo bot, e solo allora riceverai le battaglie da giocare. Per richiedere le battaglie dovrai mandare una richiesta HTTP del tipo:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">http://<u>server</u>.orionsbelt.eu/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx?type=<u>botGetBattles</u>&amp;botId=<u>1111</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>

    Nota che dovrai mandare la richiesta al server giusto. Avrai un bot per ogni server, quindi se sei registrato a più server dovrai tenerne conto nello sviluppo. Dovrai anche dare al bot un ID e un codice di verifica.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Schieramento</h2>
    La prima parte della battaglia è lo [Deploy]. Quando richiedi una battaglia con l'URL precedente, ottieni una risposta del tipo:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339260' state='<u>deploy</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='203'&gt;<u>nunos</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;Bot001&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Units&gt;
    &lt;Unit quantity='10' name='Raptor' code='rp' /&gt;
  &lt;/Units&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Questa è una battaglia molto semplice tra <u>Bot001</u> e <u>nunos</u>, e devi fare lo schieramento. La [Fleet] della battaglia ha solo i [Raptor], nessun'altra [CombatUnits]. Devi ora mandare una richiesta al <u>ResponseUrl</u> indicando come vuoi eseguire lo [Deploy]:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botdeploy</u>&amp;id=<u>1234</u>&amp;moves=<u>p:rp-8_1-2;p:rp-8_2-8;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    Il parametro <u>moves</u> è il più importante e ha il seguente formato:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">p:<u>codice_unità</u>-<u>coordinate</u>-<u>quantità</u></pre>
    Dovrai costruire una stringa come questa per ogni blocco di unità nella zona di schieramento. Trovi i codici delle unità nelle  <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">specifiche delle unità</a>. Dopo aver chiamato l'URL correttamente formato la battaglia continuerà.

    <a name=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Movimenti del turno</h2>
    Dopo lo schieramento devi chiedere nuovamente per le battaglie, e dovrai ora effettuare le tue mosse. Nota che in questi esempi viene restituita solo una battaglia, ma se avessi più battaglie da giocare riceveresti più elementi &lt;Battle/&gt;. Quando è il tuo turno di giocare ricevi qualcosa di questo tipo:
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339264' state='<u>battle</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='204'&gt;<u>tsousa</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Elements&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='2_4' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='1' ownerId='204' direction='S' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='8_1' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='0' ownerId='1339159' direction='N' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
  &lt;/Elements&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
    Nota che lo stato è cambiato da <u>deploy</u> (schieramento) a <u>battle</u> (battaglia). A questo punto ricevi la disposizione sulla [GameBoard], ogni gruppo di unità, quantità, coordinate, etc.
    Dopo aver calcolato le tue mosse dovrai mandare una risposta al server usando il <u>ResponseUrl</u>. Un esempio di URL è:
    
    <pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botbattle</u>&amp;id=<u>1111</u>&amp;moves=<u>r:7_3-n-w;b:7_3-7_2;m:8_3-8_2-5-n;b:8_2-7_2;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
    
    Il parametro <u>moves</u> è ancora una volta una lista di movimenti con la seguente sintassi:

    <table class=" + '"' + @"table" + '"' + @" style=" + '"' + @"width: 100%; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" + '"' + @"><tbody><tr><th>Tipo</th><th>Sintassi</th><th>Descrizione</th></tr><tr><td>Movimento</td><td><pre>m:<u>coordinate_unità</u>-<u>coordinate_destinazione</u>-<u>quantità</u>-<u>direzione</u>;</pre></td><td>Muove un gruppo di unità da una casella ad una adiacente</td></tr><tr><td>Rotazione</td><td><pre>r:<u>coordinate_unità</u>-<u>direzione_corrente</u>-<u>direzione_successiva</u>;</pre></td><td>Ruota un gruppo di unità; la direzione può essere: N, S, E e W</td></tr><tr><td>Attacco</td><td><pre>b:<u>coordinate_unità</u>-<u>coordinate_bersaglio</u>;</pre></td><td>Attacca un gruppo di unità avversarie</td></tr></tbody></table>
    
    A questo punto è il turno del tuo avversario. Quando finirà riceverai il nuovo stato della [GameBoard] e dovrai fare altre mosse. Questo continua sinchè la battaglia non è finita. Nota che non puoi usare più di 6 [MovPoints].
    
    <a name=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Ulteriori Informazioni</h2>
    Se hai qualche domanda o suggerimento contattaci, saremo felici di aiutarti.
  </div>");
			Add("pt", "BattleAPIInfo_Part1", @"<div class=" + '"' + @"content" + '"' + @"><a href=" + '"' + @"../../en/API/Battle.aspx" + '"' + @">Este artigo só está disponível em Inglês</a>.
  </div>");
			Add("ro", "BattleAPIInfo_Part1", @"<div class=" + '"' + @"content" + '"' + @"><b>API de luptă</b> permite aplicaţii terţe pentru a juca luptele pe [OB] ca un <i>bot</i>.
    Puteţi folosi acest API pentru a crea roboti cu inteligenta artificiala, sau clienti de joc
    care vor putea sa lupte cu alti jucatori, sau roboti pe [GameBoard]. Exemplu de luptă:
    <img src=" + '"' + @"/Resources/Images/Battle.png" + '"' + @" class=" + '"' + @"block" + '"' + @" /><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Apply" + '"' + @">How to Apply</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Overview" + '"' + @">Overview</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#AskBattles" + '"' + @">Ask For Battles</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#Deploy" + '"' + @">Deploy</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#TurnMoves" + '"' + @">Turn Moves</a></li><li><a href=" + '"' + @"#More" + '"' + @">More Information</a></li></ul><a name=" + '"' + @"Apply" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"apply" + '"' + @"></a><h2>How to Apply</h2>
    Pentru a putea să dezvolti o aplicaţie care sa foloseasca API de luptă, va trebui să ne
    contactezi. Apoi iti vom pregăti mediul de dezvoltare ca sa poti incepe.
    <p />
    Poţi să ne contactezi folosind <a href=" + '"' + @"mailto:manual@orionsbelt.eu" + '"' + @">manual@orionsbelt.eu</a><a name=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Overview" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Overview</h2>
    API de luptă este foarte simplu de utilizat. Poţi crea o aplicaţie care va comunica cu [OB] şi va trimite/primi deplasari si statusurile luptelor.
    Va trebui să-ţi codezi aplicatia pentru a efectua punerea in joc si tururile.
    Interacţiunea de baza este urmatoarea: <ul><li>#1 Intrebi server-ul pentru lupte, si primesti un fisier XML cu luptele pe care le ai de jucat</li><li>#2 Pentru fiecare bătălie primita vei trimite o cerere HTTP cu punerea in joc sau mutari la un URL dat</li><li>#3 Aşteptaţi un timp şi apoi reveniţi la pasul #1</li></ul><p />
Aveţi la dispoziţie un fişier XML cu o completa <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>. Când iti vom configura robotul/clientul vei fi capabil de a crea un joc [Friendly] cu el şi să vă încercaţi robotul în acţiune.

<a name=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"AskBattles" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Ask For Battles</h2>
Prima dată când cereti lupte, nu veti primi nimic. Va trebui să creaţi un [Friendly] cu robotul, şi numai atunci veţi obţine câteva bătălii pentru a juca. Pentru a cere lupte veţi face o solicitare HTTP pentru a:

<pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">http://<u>server</u>.orionsbelt.eu/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx?type=<u>botGetBattles</u>&amp;botId=<u>1111</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>

Reţineţi că trebuie sa trimiteti cererea pentru server-ul corect. Veţi avea un robot pe server, aşa că dacă sunteţi înregistrat pe mai mult de un server va trebui să acţionati corespunzator. Va trebui sa furnizati ID-ul robotului cat şi codul de verificare.

<a name=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"Deploy" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Deploy</h2>
Prima parte a luptei este [Deploy]. Când cereti lupte folosind URL-ul anterior veţi primi ceva de genul:
<pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339260' state='<u>deploy</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='203'&gt;<u>nunos</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;Bot001&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Units&gt;
    &lt;Unit quantity='10' name='Raptor' code='rp' /&gt;
  &lt;/Units&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
Aceasta este o foarte simplă luptă între <u>Bot001</u> şi <u>nunos</u>, şi trebuie sa deplasati piesele pe tabla. [Fleet] luptatoare are doar [Raptor], nu mai sunt prezente nici o [CombatUnits]. Acum trebuie să faceti o cerere catre <u>ResponseUrl</u> indicand modul în care doriţi să [Deploy]:
<pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botdeploy</u>&amp;id=<u>1234</u>&amp;moves=<u>p:rp-8_1-2;p:rp-8_2-8;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
Parametrul <u>moves</u> este cel mai important şi are următorul format:
<pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">p:<u>unit_code</u>-<u>coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u></pre>
Trebuie sa construiti un sir ca acesta pentru fiecare unitate de bloc din zona de depuneri a pieselor. Aveti unitate de coduri pe <a href=" + '"' + @"UnitsJSON.aspx" + '"' + @">units specification</a>.
După invocarea URL-ului corect, lupta va continua.

<a name=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"TurnMoves" + '"' + @"></a><h2>Turn Moves</h2>
Dupa depunerea pieselor puteti cere din nou luptele dumneavoastra, iar acum va trebui sa va jucati miscarile. Reţineţi că in aceste exemple doar o luptă este returnata, dar dacă aţi avut mai multe lupte jucate vei primi mai multe elemente &lt;Battle/&gt;. Atunci când este rândul tău să joci, vei primi ceva de genul:
<pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @">
  &lt;Battles&gt;
    &lt;Battle id='1339264' state='<u>battle</u>'&gt;
  &lt;ResponseUrl&gt;http://source_server/Ajax/Battle/BotBattle.ashx&lt;/ResponseUrl&gt;
  &lt;Players&gt;
    &lt;Player id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
    &lt;Player id='1' ownerId='204'&gt;<u>tsousa</u>&lt;/Player&gt;
  &lt;/Players&gt;
  &lt;CurrentPlayer id='0' ownerId='1339159'&gt;<u>Bot001</u>&lt;/CurrentPlayer&gt;
  &lt;Elements&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='2_4' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='1' ownerId='204' direction='S' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
    &lt;Element coordinate='8_1' canBeMoved='True' canUseSpecialHabilities='True' 
  id='0' ownerId='1339159' direction='N' quantity='1' remainingDefense='300' code='rp'/&gt;
  &lt;/Elements&gt;
    &lt;/Battle&gt;
  &lt;/Battles&gt;
    </pre>
Reţineţi că statutul s-a schimbat de la <u>deploy</u> la <u>battle</u>. Acum veţi primi dispunearea corecta a [GameBoard], fiecare grup de unitati, cantitatea, coordonatele, etc.
După calcularea mutarilor, trebuie sa trimite-ti raspunsul din nou la joc cu ajutorul <u>ResponseUrl</u>. Un exemplu de URL-ul ar fi:
<pre class=" + '"' + @"code" + '"' + @"><u>[ResponseUrl]</u>?type=<u>botbattle</u>&amp;id=<u>1111</u>&amp;moves=<u>r:7_3-n-w;b:7_3-7_2;m:8_3-8_2-5-n;b:8_2-7_2;</u>&amp;botId=<u>321</u>&amp;verificationCode=<u>ABC</u></pre>
Parametrul <u>moves</u> este din nou o listă cu mutari cu următoarea sintaxă:
<table class=" + '"' + @"table" + '"' + @" style=" + '"' + @"width:100%;margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;" + '"' + @"><tr><th>Type</th><th>Syntax</th><th>Description</th></tr><tr><td>Move</td><td><pre>m:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>destination_coordinate</u>-<u>quantity</u>-<u>direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Moves a unit group from one square to another adjacent square</td></tr><tr><td>Rotate</td><td><pre>r:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>current_direction</u>-<u>next_direction</u>;</pre></td><td>Rotates a unit group; direction can be: N, S, E and W</td></tr><tr><td>Attack</td><td><pre>b:<u>unit_coordinate</u>-<u>target_coordinate</u>;</pre></td><td>Attacks the adversary unit group</td></tr></table>
Apoi este randul oponentului pentru a juca. Când este gata, veţi primi noua [GameBoard] şi trebuie sa executati alte mutari. Aceasta va continua până cand lupta nu este terminata.
Reţineţi că mutarile nu pot consuma mai mult de 6 [MovPoints].
<a name=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @" id=" + '"' + @"More" + '"' + @"></a><h2>More Information</h2>
